      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "1. On 11 July 1947, [REDACTED] 170th",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "AAF Base Unit, Ferry Division, Brooks Field, San Antonio, Texas was",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "interviewed and the following information was obtained: [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "departed Williams Field, Arizona at 1400 CST on 28 June 1947 in a P-51",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "for Portland, Oregon, by the way of Medford, Oregon. At approximately",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "1515 CST on a course of 300 degrees, and ground speed of 285, altitude",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "10,000 feet, approximately thirty miles northwest of Lake Meade, Nevada",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "[REDACTED] sighted five or six white, circular objects at four o'clock,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "altitude approximately 6,000 feet, course approximately 120 degrees and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "an estimated speed of 285 MPH. [REDACTED] said the objects were flying",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "very smoothly and in a close formation. The estimated size of the white",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "objects were approximately 36 inches in diameter. [REDACTED] stated",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "that he is sure the white objects were not birds, since the rate of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "closure was very fast. Lt. Armstrong was certain that the white objects",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "were not jets or conventional type aircraft since he has flown both types.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "AGENT'S NOTES:",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "[REDACTED] was very sincere in his explanation and was not the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
